I"Ú<p>Filip Biljecki, who successfully completed earlier this year his PhD in our group, is the <a href="http://www.eurosdr.net/news/eurosdr-award-winner-2017">winner of the second EuroSDR award for the best PhD thesis</a> related to geoinformation science!
<a href="http://www.eurosdr.net">EuroSDR</a> is a not-for-profit organisation linking National Mapping and Cadastral Agencies with Research Institutes and Universities in Europe for the purpose of applied research in spatial data provision, management and delivery.</p>

<p>Filip won the award for his thesis <a href="http://filipbiljecki.com/phd/dissertationFilipBiljecki.pdf">Level of Detail in 3D City Models</a>.
The PhD was already ranked among the 5% best theses of Delft University of Technology.</p>

<p>Filip is currently a postdoc at the National University of Singapore.</p>

<p>Many congratulations, Filip!</p>

